# Netlify / Cloudflare Pages proxy rules.
#
# The SPA calls same-origin /__portal/... (see gateway.proxy in
# config/site.config.ts). These rules proxy that prefix to the admission portal
# at the CDN edge, so the browser sees same-origin responses (no CORS) and the
# frontend code is identical to `pnpm dev`.
#
#   status 200  = proxy (fetch the target server-side and return its response)
#
# NOTE: GitHub Pages does NOT support proxying/rewrites — for live queries use
# Netlify, Vercel, Cloudflare Pages, or a serverless function / external proxy.
/__portal/*  https://entry.nottingham.edu.cn/:splat  200
